    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A genre of animated film or television entertainment distinctively Japanese or in Japanese-style, characterized by a visual style involving stylized action sequences and usually featuring characters with distinctive large, staring eyes, and typically having a having themes of science-fiction, fantasy, violence, or sexually explicit material.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096613/Museum of Modern Art (MoMA), New York [online] (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een genre in de animatiefilm of in televiesieamusement, in een karakteristieke Japanse of Japans-achtige stijl, met gestileerde actiesequenties en meestal met personages die typische grote, starende ogen hebben. Vaak betreft het thema's op het gebied van de sciencefiction en fantasy, en is de actie gewelddadig of seksueel expliciet.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Um gênero de filme de animação ou entretenimento de televisão nitidamente japonês ou no estilo japonês, caracterizado por um estilo visual envolvendo sequências de ação estilizadas e geralmente apresentando personagens com olhos grandes e fixos e tipicamente tendo temas de ficção científica, fantasia, violência , ou material sexualmente explícito.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
